## Phase 5a outcomes (UI migration — locked)

- `agentmarket/` now uses Tailwind v4 (CSS-first via `@tailwindcss/postcss`). No `tailwind.config.js`.
- Dark theme is forced via `<html className="dark">` in `app/layout.tsx`. `:root` light tokens exist in `globals.css` but never apply. **Do not install `next-themes` or build a theme toggle — we are dark-only.**
- Fonts: Inter + JetBrains Mono via `next/font/google` (editorial Instrument Serif theme deferred — see HANDOFF.md §8).
- Component prop signatures (post-5a, locked):
  ```tsx
  <JobCard job={job} onClaim={(id)=>...} onViewResult={(id)=>...} highlighted={false} />
  <TransactionFeed initial={txs} sseUrl="/api/events" maxItems={50} className="" />
  <LiveStats apiUrl="/api/stats" pollMs={3000} />
  ```
- `TransactionFeed` self-subscribes to `/api/events` (no parent wiring needed). `LiveStats` self-polls `/api/stats`. Phase 5b only needs to wire the marketplace job-list fetch and the post-job modal.
- `app/marketplace/page.tsx` is a Next App Router page — **cannot accept arbitrary props**. Initial data must be fetched inside the component (useEffect on mount) or via a Server Component wrapper. The original v0 `MarketplacePageProps` interface was deleted during 5a.
- `components/JobCard.tsx` uses hardcoded hex colors (e.g. `bg-[#1E293B]`) instead of token classes. Migrate to `bg-card` / `text-foreground` etc. when re-theming.
- `ui-mockup/` folder is preserved at workspace root as a reference snapshot — do not delete or edit.

## Tech debt log

Format: `route/file — issue — added in phase N`.

- `lib/lightning.ts` — `L402VerifyResult.status` was `401 \| 403`, expanded to `401 \| 402 \| 403` during 5a — phase 5a (no behavior change, just type)
- `components/JobCard.tsx` — uses hardcoded hex (`bg-[#0F172A]` etc.) instead of Tailwind theme tokens; blocks one-line theme swap — phase 5a
- `app/marketplace/page.tsx` — `handlePostJob` is fake (`setTimeout` chain); replace with real flow in 5b — phase 5a (intentional)
- `app/marketplace/page.tsx` — `useEffect` for stats polling and SSE subscription are commented-out TODOs; the component children (`LiveStats`, `TransactionFeed`) self-wire so the page-level subscriptions may not be needed — re-evaluate in 5b — phase 5a (intentional)
- `agents/worker.js` — `seen` set never re-admits a job after `process_error` (line 388 comment). Transient failures (LLM timeout, mid-flight payment race) permanently dead-letter the job for that worker process. Acceptable for demo, but a real worker should mark the job and retry once after a backoff — phase 6
- `app/api/demo/post-job/route.ts` — added 6×2.5s retry on the L402 replay step to absorb Lightning settlement lag (~5-10s). Without this the agent loses the post-job sats but no job is created (silent burn). Mirrors `worker.js claimJobWithL402` — phase 6 closing test

## Phase 6 closing test (real-money cycle, mainnet)

**Verified working end-to-end on Apr 26, 07:55 UTC.** Single QA job, reward=10 sats:

| Step | Money flow | Real settlement |
|---|---|---|
| Requester posts job (L402 11 sats) | agent → marketplace | 10 sats received (1 LSP fee) |
| Worker auto-claims (L402 2 sats) | agent → marketplace | 1 sat received (1 LSP fee) |
| Worker calls Groq llama-3.3-70b | (off-chain) | result="HELLO" in <1s |
| Worker generates payout invoice 10 sats | — | — |
| Worker posts /deliver | marketplace pays agent's invoice | 9 sats received (1 LSP fee) |

Net per cycle: agent ≈ -4 sats, marketplace ≈ +1 sat, LSP ≈ +3 sats. Total settlement time post→deliver ≈ 23s.
